 `super.resolveClass` fails. It’s crucial to get these details right!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring bytecode options**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I can avoid using NestHost by generating bytes from a top-level enum. It seems like this could be simpler with less risk, but I think it would need a compile step. However, maybe I can generate bytecode from the existing build without using a top-level enum. I’ll look for any top-level enum class in the build test with a short name just to see what I can find.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TAolx3UuWlJ5BuQsKr11LH2n|fc_0ed54e5b365aaa350169f58f7e712881a08f5924a72e8d8ccc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test -name '*.class' | grep -v '\\$' | head -10", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2080, "output": 1393, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35729, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777700713847, "responseId": "resp_0ed54e5b365aaa350169f58f6a51b481a0b07992194c5b983a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_TAolx3UuWlJ5BuQsKr11LH2n|fc_0ed54e5b365aaa350169f58f7e712881a08f5924a72e8d8ccc", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/ReflectionHelperTest.class\ntests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/LinkedHashMapCustomFieldSerializerTest.class\ntests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/ServerSerializationStreamWriterTest.class\ntests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test/org_gwtproject/gwt_user/AbstractLocalizableImplCreatorTest.class\ntests/src/org.gwtproject/gwt-user/2.11.0/build/classes/java/test/org_gwtproject/gw